# Use Bun Instead of npm

Always use `bun` commands instead of `npm` commands for package management and script execution.

## Command Mappings

- Use `bun install` instead of `npm install`
- Use `bun add <package>` instead of `npm install <package>`
- Use `bun remove <package>` instead of `npm uninstall <package>`
- Use `bun run <script>` instead of `npm run <script>`
- Use `bun <script>` instead of `npm run <script>` (bun can run scripts directly)
- Use `bun dev` instead of `npm run dev`
- Use `bun build` instead of `npm run build`
- Use `bun test` instead of `npm test`

## Examples

**Package Installation:**
```bash
# ✅ Correct
bun install
bun add react
bun add -d typescript

# ❌ Avoid
npm install
npm install react
npm install -D typescript
```

**Script Execution:**
```bash
# ✅ Correct
bun dev
bun build
bun test
bun run start

# ❌ Avoid
npm run dev
npm run build
npm test
npm start
```

## Notes

- Bun is faster and more efficient than npm
- Bun has better compatibility with modern JavaScript/TypeScript projects
- Always prefer bun commands in documentation, scripts, and terminal suggestions